                <h1>Are Background Checks and Fingerprints the Same? Explained</h1>
                <p>Background checks and fingerprinting are not the same, though they often complement each other. A background check is a broad assessment of a person’s history, including criminal records, employment, and credit. Fingerprinting specifically records an individual's unique fingerprint patterns, primarily for identifying individuals in criminal programs or job assessments.</p>
